# Part 2 — Describe a movie you watched recently.

Recently, I watched a movie called *Interstellar*, which is a very famous science-fiction film directed by Christopher Nolan. I watched it about two weeks ago in my dormitory with one of my roommates. We decided to watch it on a Friday night after finishing our assignments because we both enjoy movies related to technology and space exploration.

The movie is mainly about a group of astronauts who travel through space to find another planet for humans to live on, since the Earth is gradually becoming uninhabitable. What impressed me most was that the film combined advanced scientific theories with emotional family relationships. For example, it explored concepts like black holes, time dilation, and artificial intelligence, but at the same time, it also focused heavily on the emotional connection between a father and his daughter.

I chose to watch this movie because many people online described it as one of the best sci-fi films ever made. Besides that, as a computer science student, I’m naturally curious about futuristic technology and the future of humanity, so the topic really appealed to me. Another reason is that I personally enjoy movies that make me think deeply instead of just providing simple entertainment.

Overall, I really enjoyed the movie. The visual effects were incredible, the soundtrack was powerful, and the story was emotionally moving. After watching it, I kept thinking about it for several days. It even made me more interested in science and space research.

### 中文：

最近我看了一部叫《星际穿越》的电影，这是一部非常著名的科幻电影，由克里斯托弗·诺兰导演。大概是两周前，我和一个室友在宿舍里看的。我们是在周五晚上完成作业之后决定看的，因为我们都喜欢和科技、太空探索有关的电影。

这部电影主要讲的是一群宇航员前往太空，为人类寻找新的宜居星球，因为地球正在逐渐变得不适合生存。最让我印象深刻的是，这部电影把先进的科学理论和家庭情感结合得很好。比如它探讨了黑洞、时间膨胀和人工智能等概念，同时也重点描写了父亲和女儿之间的情感联系。

我选择看这部电影，是因为很多网友都说它是史上最好的科幻电影之一。此外，作为一名计算机专业学生，我本身就对未来科技和人类未来发展很感兴趣，所以这个主题特别吸引我。还有一个原因是，我喜欢那些能引发思考，而不仅仅是单纯娱乐的电影。

总的来说，我非常喜欢这部电影。它的视觉效果特别震撼，配乐也非常有感染力，而且故事十分感人。看完之后，我连续好几天都在思考它，甚至让我对科学和太空研究更加感兴趣了。

